node_modules/
.env
.env.local
dist/
build/
.DS_Store
*.tsbuildinfo

# Root-level tool state. Only machine-local / derived / regenerated paths under
# /.code-pact/ are ignored; the shared config (project.yaml, agent/model
# profiles, state/baselines) is committed. Anchored with / so
# tests/fixtures/**/.code-pact/ is not affected.
# Ignored exceptions specific to this repo:
#  - state/progress.yaml (legacy ONLY — NOT state/events/). The per-event ledger
#    under state/events/ IS committed here, exactly as a user project commits it:
#    it is the shared, merge-safe operational state this RFC made conflict-free,
#    and committing it is what lets this repo dogfood the CI branch-drift gate
#    (collaboration-safe-state RFC A3 / Resolved Q1). Only the legacy *monolithic*
#    progress.yaml stays ignored — it is the maintainer's pre-event-file history,
#    read-merged locally; per RFC A3 it stays ignored until per-event files
#    replace it (committing the monolithic file would reintroduce the very merge
#    problem the event ledger fixes).
#  - adapters/ — this repo is the SOURCE of the adapter templates and regenerates
#    CLAUDE.md / .claude/skills/* (ignored below), so committing the manifest
#    alone would orphan it (clean checkout -> ADAPTER_FILE_MISSING in adapter
#    doctor). Manifest and its generated files travel together or not at all.
/.code-pact/locks/
/.code-pact/cache/
/.code-pact/state/progress.yaml
/.code-pact/adapters/

# Root-level generated context output
/.context/

# Root-level adapter-generated output (regenerable via `adapter upgrade`;
# ignored independently of the .code-pact policy above).
/CLAUDE.md
/AGENTS.md
/GEMINI.md
/.claude/
/.codex/
/.cursor/

# Generated context inside test fixtures (written by pack tests)
tests/fixtures/**/.context/

# Root-level private design notes (planning, strategy, retro)
/.local/
*.tgz

# Per-maintainer SSH allowedSigners for `git verify-tag`. Intentionally
# not committed in v0.2 (single-maintainer); see CONTRIBUTING.md.
.git_allowed_signers
